==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Durra
<hw>Dur"ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ar.
<ets>dhorra</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A kind of millet,
cultivated throughout Asia, and introduced into the south of Europe; a
variety of <spn>Sorghum vulgare</spn>; -- called also <altname>Indian
millet</altname>, and <altname>Guinea corn</altname>.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>dhoorra</asp>, <asp>dhurra</asp>,
<asp>doura</asp>, etc.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Durst</ent>⟦br⟧
